## 1. Definitions and Classification

"Library Code" means components, SDKs, reusable modules, and related
source/objects primarily intended to be linked to or called by other software.

"Project Code" means complete applications/services, together with
build/deploy scripts and operational assets primarily intended to deliver
end-user functionality.

File-level determination:

- An SPDX header prevails when present:
  - `SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT` means Library Code.
  - `SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later` means Project Code.
- If no SPDX header is present, conventional paths may guide:
  - `app/`, `server/`, `scripts/`, `public/`, `docs/` are Project Code unless
    explicitly marked otherwise.
  - `lib/`, `libs/`, `sdk/`, `plugins/`, and package-style reusable modules are
    Library Code unless explicitly marked otherwise.

Merely combining Library Code and Project Code in the same repository or
distribution does not change each part's license.

