## 4. Additional Terms for Project Code

These additional terms apply only to files licensed as Project Code under
AGPL-3.0-or-later and are intended to be compatible with GPLv3/AGPLv3 Section 7.

### 4.1 UI Attribution and Appropriate Legal Notice

When Project Code runs with an interactive user interface, locally or as a
network service, you must display an Appropriate Legal Notice in at least one
prominent location containing:

Powered by Curatory - Source: https://github.com/KennKyou/Curatory - License: AGPL-3.0-or-later

A prominent location is satisfied by any of:

- an About dialog/page;
- a signed-in home or footer;
- a Settings page;
- an equivalent persistent help/about location.

Text may be localized and styled to match the product, but must remain
reasonably visible at common resolutions.

Modified deployments should replace the source URL with a link to the exact
Corresponding Source for the running version.

API-only services with no human-facing UI must expose a machine-readable
endpoint, such as `/legal` or `/about`, returning the same attribution and a
link to the exact Corresponding Source.

Non-interactive CLIs that only print logs are exempt.

### 4.2 Modification Notice

You must state changes you make to Project Code, including the date of change,
in a reasonable place in the source, such as a CHANGELOG or per-file header.

### 4.3 No Additional Restrictions

These additional terms do not expand copyright scope, do not alter the
definition of Corresponding Source, and do not impose further restrictions
beyond those permitted by GPLv3/AGPLv3 Section 7. In case of conflict, the
AGPL-3.0-or-later text controls.

